collections.description:
In the Depths of Crypto's Legendary Waters...
            Beneath the waves of volatility, where only the boldest dare to dive, lies the League of Eternal HODLers—a secret society where whales, dolphins, and sharks reign supreme, adorned with bling that tells tales of their trading prowess. Each accessory is more than just a statement piece; it’s a badge of honor, representing their unyielding faith in the hexagonal tides of blockchain treasure.
            
            The Accessories of the Abyss:
        
            Diamond-Tier Drip: For the gods of liquidity. Whether it’s a hat that catches the sparkle of starlit block confirmations or a cane that strikes fear into bearish trends, this tier screams, “I’ll never sell.”
            Gold Chains & Silver Bracelets: Worn by those who HODL through stormy markets with grace, each link forged from the molten gains of FOMO'd altcoins.
            Bronze Bling: Battle scars of early trades and lessons learned, a symbol of resilience.

collections.name: Classical Reveries (ArtWorks-Collection)
collections.description:
Classical Reveries (ArtWorks-Collection)
A Visual Symphony Inspired by Music

This collection features high-quality digital cover artworks inspired by the emotional depth of my instrumental music. Each piece visually captures the essence of Classical, Neo-Classical, New Age, and Orchestral Landscapes, bringing a soulful and melancholic aesthetic to life.

What Makes This Collection Unique?

🎨 Fine Art & Music Fusion – Each artwork is deeply connected to my original compositions or unique arrangements, offering collectors a visual extension of my music.
🖼️ Exclusive Digital Artwork – Own a collectible piece of art that reflects timeless melodies and emotions.
📂 Unlockable Content – Select pieces include high-resolution downloads and behind-the-scenes creation insights.

Perfect for music enthusiasts, digital art collectors, and NFT lovers, this collection serves as a standalone art series or a visual companion to my music NFTs.

collections.name: a2p-v2
collections.description:
We are running an experiment called a2p. It’s a speculative exploration into new ways of distributing and sharing digital images, videos, and animations. We’re a group of artists selected by three artists/curators: myself (Los Angeles), Iris Long (Beijing), and Carol Sabbadini (Bogotá).

Each of us has created a new artwork and has released it as an edition of ten along with one artist proof. We’re across many time zones and continents, but for one week, we’ll occupy a shared online space where we’ll trade work. It’s a performance, but also a way of sharing our work with fellow artists and a way to think about what happens to the work after it’s made. It’s an artist-to-artist system to build and curate a collection of work.
